               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-819" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-819" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-819" type="surname" value="WEEKS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-819" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>ANN WEEKS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the wife of Benjamin Weeks, a tobacconist, in Dean-street, Westminster—on the 3rd of Feb. the prisoner came and bought some<lb></lb>thing—he paid me half-a-crown—I put it in my drawer—I afterwards gave it to my husband; he bent it, and laid it in the same drawer again—I after<lb></lb>wards gave it to the policeman—it had not been mixed with any other coin.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">COURT</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Was there any other half-crown in the drawer? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> She says it was on the 3rd of Feb. and it was on the 1st—I went in for half an ounce of tobacco.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-820" type="witnessName">
