                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-821" type="given" value="SARAH"></interp>SARAH GLOVER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a cow-keeper. On the 15th of Feb. I saw a person, but I really cannot recollect the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-822" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-822" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-822" type="surname" value="GLOVER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-822" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE GLOVER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the son of Sarah Glover. On the 15th of Feb. the prisoner came into my mother's shop, and for what he bought he tendered my mother a counterfeit half-crown—I detained him, and when the officer passed I gave him into custody, with the half-crown—I am sure it was the one the prisoner gave to my mother, and she brought it to me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18430227-name-823" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-823" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-823" type="surname" value="DUNT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18430227-name-823" type="given" value="ADAM"></interp>ADAM DUNT</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable B</hi> 170.) On the 15th of Feb. the prisoner was given into my custody—I took him to Queen-square, and he was let out on his own recognizances to appear on the Monday following, but he did not come—I took him next day—this is the half-crown I received from Mr. Glover.</p>
               <p>
